A 35-year-old mechanic, Akintunde Iwayemi, at the weekend appeared at an Okitipupa Magistratesâ€™ Court in Ondo State for allegedly stealing two goats valued at N25,000. The defendant, whose address was not given, is standing trial on a two-count charge of felony and stealing. Prosecuting Inspector Zedekiah Orogbemi alleged that the defendant last December 17 around 5:30am, at Ayeka New Site in Okitipupa, conspired with one other at large to commit the act. He alleged that the defendant stole the goats belonging to Abass Aladeloye, where they were kept. The prosecutor said that the offence contravened sections 516 and 390(9) of the Criminal Code Laws of Ondo State, 2006. The defendant pleaded not guilty. Chief Magistrate Mr. Musa Al-Yunus admitted him to bail in the sum of N50,000, with a surety in the like sum. He said that the surety must show evidence of one year tax payment to the Ondo State Government and adjourned the case till January 30 for further hearing.